name: Girl next door
review: I have long but not curling lashes, this is the best curler I have yet to come across. I use it before and after applying mascara and my curl last all day. Some days I'm not feeling the mascara so I'll use it to just curl my natural eyelashes bit doing that usually requires me to curl again mid day.

name: Allie
review: I really like this curler alot. It doesn't pull lashes. They seem to hold the curl and my eyes look much bigger. I recommend it definitely!

review: Gets the job done.

review: the opening is too big and pinches the corner of the eye.

name: Trinaty

review: My daughter and I both had extreme difficulty in using this eyelash curler, to the point of pinching the skin and never getting our lashes to curl.  We actually gave up and bought our old one we've used for years.  We only bought this one because of the bling and we thought it would curl our lashes even better than our old stand-by, but we were wrong.

review: Does not girl your eyelashes. Don't be fooled into buying this like I was because it's cute and had rhinestones, those are the only pros about this thing.

name: Lexi on the go
review: Great eyelash curler....one of the best.

name: Madelyn
review: Regardless of your eye shape and size, this simply doesn't curl, even if heated first.

name: Deborah
review: When I first bought this I was disappointed, it wasn't the same kind of Revlon eyelash curler I had in the past. The one I had, that I loved had a spring attached to it.  When I used it the first two times it didn't work. But after using it for a week it started to curl my eyelashes. Idk if it was just my eyelashes or the rubber insert needed time to mold to my eye but it is great now. I have the expensive brands and honestly you can't beat the price for these. I will definitely continue to use Revlon eyelash curlers

name: Edie
review: We tried the product and neither of us liked it at all. We both went back to our old products

review: I use this product on a daily basis to make my eyelashes look longer and more defined. I love it and it works really good.

name: Shawn
review:
I purchased this to replace an eye lash curler that is about 25 years old. I will keep using my antique eyelash curler, as this one does not curl my lashes.
I guess the old adage is true...."they don't make them like they used to".

name: pearl
review:
I will be returning this product back to store, it
is a bulky item, unable to get to the lashes like the other lash curlers i have had in the past.

name: HairCareGuru
review: It doesn't stick to lashes that already have mascara on them, it's fabulous.

name: Heather
review: This was my first foray into eyelash curlers and it was not a good one. I have a pretty standard eye shape, not too small but not too large, and this did not fit the shape of my eye very well. I do not have the longest eyelashes and found it very difficult to get my eyelashes in the contraption (couldn't get it close enough to the root of my lashes). Aside from not fitting the shape of my eye very well it also did not curl well. I heated it up a lil bit with my blow dryer hoping that would help hold the curl better and that did not work at all. I applied mascara (Clinique Chubby Lash mascara) as fast as I could and they were up a lil bit more than normal but by the end of the day they were back to their normal shape. Save up some money and buy a better curler.

name: product junkie
review: I really like this lash curler once I got used to it. It has a pretty deep curve to it and my lashes are not real long. But now that i am used to it I like the curl I get from it.

name: cali girl
review: Did not curl my eyelashes

name: Me
review: None

review: My lashes aren't very long, so I need a little help with a curler.  After applying mascara, my lashes do appear longer.  Easy to use.

review: Bought this on sale. Thought it was pretty. The plastic handle inserts fell out after one use, and the curler didn't curl my lashes. Seemed to be sized too big.

review: Works great! Curls the lashes,doesn't give them a kink like some lash curlers. Fits the eye well, if that makes sense.
